# part 8: Network management
1- Open port 443 , 80
2- Make the changes permanent
3- Block ssh connection for your colleague ip to the VM.

firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=http      # Open HTTP port (80) permanently
firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=https     # Open HTTPS port (443) permanently
firewall-cmd --reload                            # Reload firewall to apply the new rules
firewall-cmd --permanent --add-rich-rule='rule family="ipv4" source address="192.168.1.100" port protocol="tcp" port="22" reject' Block SSH (port 22) permanently for colleague IP 192.168.1.100
firewall-cmd --reload                            # Reload firewall to apply the SSH block
firewall-cmd --list-all                          # List all firewall rules to verify the configuration

notes:
Port 80: HTTP (HyperText Transfer Protocol). Used for normal, unencrypted web traffic. Port 443: HTTPS (HTTP Secure). Used for secure, encrypted web traffic. Opening them allows users to access websites hosted on the server.
A firewall is a security system that controls and filters network traffic to protect servers and networks.
Block ssh connection for your colleague ip to the VM. To prevent unauthorized or restricted users from accessing the server via SSH.


